<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>In the reference guide of Zend_Application in the <a href="http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/zend.application.examples.html">examples section</a>, I found the following snippet:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
class Bootstrap extends Zend_Application_Bootstrap_Bootstrap
{
    protected function _initRequest(array $options = array())
    {
        ...
    }
}
</code></pre>

<p>I was trying to find the utility of {{$options}}, since it is not passed by the calls to {{bootstrap()}} and {{bootstrap()}}. Also, in the snippet, the $options array isn't used.</p>

<p>Reading {{Zend_Application_Bootstrap_BootstrapAbstract}}, the {{_init}} method isn't called with additional arguments. This can confuse some people, specially if trying the overloaded way.</p>

<p>As a hint, look the following methods of {{Zend_Application_Bootstrap_BootstrapAbstract}}:</p>

<ul><li>{{__call}}</li>
<li>{{bootstrap}}</li>
<li>{{_bootstrap}}</li>
<li>{{_executeResource}}</li>
</ul>
